						<summary>

						<p>On a fragmentary some lying outside the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> on the west side of the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>KUMĀRA ANANTHARĀJA.</p>						

						<p>RUDHIRŌDGĀRI.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in cyclic year Rudhirōdgāri, Kārttīka, śu. 10. On the basis of palaecgraphy and internal evidence it can be assigned to 16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This incomplete record mention the king <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Maṭli Kumāra Anantharājayyadēva Chōḍa mahārāja and his <hi rend="italic">Kāryakarna.</hi></p>						

